To apply Mendelian randomization to samples of siblings, effect estimates for the SNP-exposure association and SNP-outcome association are based on correlating the phenotypic divergence with the genotypic divergence within sibling pairs. Taking the difference between siblings removes the effect of the family-level confounder. For any pair of siblings within family k, indicated k,1 and k,2, the genotypic difference at genetic variant j is:3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
